text: Why is the movie 3D?  I will tell you.  CGI is a background effect only unless it is used to create something unnatural in the foreground (like a transformer, android, ghost or special effect), if you generate something natural.. well, recognisable (such as a person or a building) in the foreground where the viewers attention is focused they will immediately not accept it, the brain notices patterns, markings, shadings, shadows, lighting effects, angles and a host of other stuff that we are not consciously aware of.  The result is something unnatural will stand out a mile.  This effect is known as the 'Uncanny valley' and you noticed it the moment they reached the top of the tower and you scanned the rooftop, regardless of your familiarity with 9/11.  By making the movie 3D the movie will purposely be slightly out of focus due to the 3D effect and your brain will also know you are watching a fake 3D image anyway, both of these will help offset your rejection of the CGI.

text: This write up is a for those who care about what they watch-  As a common visitor to the original World Trade center, it is absolutely remarkable how Sony was able to re-create the WTC to exactly what it looked like in 1974.  The only thing I noticed right away was the clouds during frames 1:03- 1:17.  The clouds seem to skip frames though it's surroundings do not.  Another improvement that could be made is the darkness of the interior in both towers, there could be more depth, giving us a better look inside the towers.  The windows were tinted, but you could probably see more through the windows in that weather on the actual day.  My rating is 10/10.  Minimal improvements could be added to make this movie a perfect example of great green screen use.

text: I typed up the addresses, for letters occasionally that would go above the 90th floor or higher, from Los Angeles. This was back in 1998 or 1999. I mentioned to two coworkers that I was amazed that this letter would go across country and then up so high. I was not only made fun of but ridiculed. They laughed at me. These buildings were not admired by most people at that time. Nobody back then would even think of making a movie like this. One of the coworkers, who was a russian immigrant, said he was up there and that it was no big deal even. Amazing really, if you just think about it.

text: Movie was great and enjoyed it, watched it today by myself without any distractions, weekends are terrible with teenagers doing stupid things as usual. Great actors and performances, and I already knew the true story about this before, watched it on the History Channel or something a while back. I don't think the movie is the same as the real story though. They might have added some additional scenes near the end. But overall, it was a great movie, very brave man who had so much tenacity to pull this dangerous death defying stunt. Graphics and background scenery looked very realistic with green screen technology, etc. He got what he wanted, but with a heavy price. World Trade Center was an engineering marvel, researched it before it was attacked by terrorists on 09/11 and collapsed.
